00:00:55.922 --> 00:00:58.925
So what are expressions?

00:00:59.259 --> 00:01:03.696
Expressions are a powerful
scripting feature

00:01:03.963 --> 00:01:09.135
that allows you to automate animation,
create complex motion graphics

00:01:09.335 --> 00:01:12.572
and link properties together dynamically.

00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:17.844
They are written in a scripting language
based on JavaScript.

00:01:18.011 --> 00:01:21.014
Extending the functionality
of the software

00:01:21.247 --> 00:01:24.350
beyond simple keyframe based animation.

00:01:26.653 --> 00:01:28.188
Now let's talk about

00:01:28.188 --> 00:01:31.191
expressions versus keyframes.

00:01:31.191 --> 00:01:34.494
Why should I use expressions
and not keyframe?

00:01:35.128 --> 00:01:40.200
Well, keyframes provide manual control
and precise adjustments,

00:01:40.433 --> 00:01:44.437
while expressions offer
automation, adaptability,

00:01:44.437 --> 00:01:48.775
and the ability to create complex
interactive animations.

00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.911
Both techniques have their strengths

00:01:51.911 --> 00:01:55.548
and using a combination of keyframes
and expressions

00:01:55.882 --> 00:01:58.551
can empower you to create

00:01:58.551 --> 00:02:02.255
stunning and dynamic animations
in After Effects.

00:02:02.789 --> 00:02:06.493
We don't use expressions
to make our lives more difficult

00:02:06.493 --> 00:02:08.561
by having to learn more things.

00:02:08.561 --> 00:02:12.232
We use expressions
to make our lives easier

00:02:12.265 --> 00:02:15.468
and have the code automate things for us.

00:02:17.804 --> 00:02:19.072
Expressions in

00:02:19.072 --> 00:02:23.309
After Effects are written in a language
based on JavaScript.

00:02:23.343 --> 00:02:27.514
So spaces don't matter too much,
but caps do.

00:02:27.981 --> 00:02:31.017
You need to write words exactly

